_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "Venezuela (cultivated by Indigenous peoples), introduced from Cayenne, French Guiana 1820, to Queensland via Kew Gardens, England 1858 and 1881", "traits": "Large cylindrical fruit 2.5-3.0 kg, smooth leaves without spines, ovoid medium-sized, turns yellow from base to top when ripening", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow to yellow, firm, close-textured, juicy, traditional pineapple flavor", "yield_notes": "Leading variety for canning, high yields, good fruit shape, 12-16° Brix, 0.5-1.0% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Queen (Common Rough)", "slug": "queen-common-rough", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "South Africa and Australia (historic cultivation), widely distributed heritage variety", "traits": "Small to medium fruit 1-1.5 kg, dwarf compact plant, spiny dark purplish-green leaves, rough skin, conical shape, deeply placed eyes", "flesh_fruit": "Deep golden-yellow, crisp, less juicy than Cayenne but more aromatic, small core, tender, fine flavor", "yield_notes": "Lower than Cayenne, early maturity, produces 2+ suckers, 15-16° Brix, 0.6-0.8% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Rough Leaf (Queen group)", "slug": "rough-leaf-queen-group", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Ripley Queen (Ripley)", "slug": "ripley-queen-ripley", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "Queensland, Australia (developed in Queensland), 20th century selection", "traits": "Dwarf compact plant, crimson-tinged leaves, reddish-green leaves with brown spots, 3-6 pounds, golden rind when ripe, pale copper when fully mature, irregular bearer", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow, non-fibrous, very sweet and rich, juicy, sweet-tart balance (13-15° Brix), low fiber", "yield_notes": "Takes 22 weeks from flowering to fruit maturity, 1.36-2.7 kg fruit", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "MacGregor (McGregor, Rough McGregor)", "slug": "macgregor-mcgregor-rough-mcgregor", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Queensland, Australia (hybridized from Smooth Cayenne in the 1980s), Australian creation", "traits": "Bright yellow rind, 4-7 pounds, square shoulders, larger fruit than typical Queen", "flesh_fruit": "Firm, sweet, low acidity, incredibly firm with more robust aroma than other Queen varieties", "yield_notes": "High productivity, disease resistant", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Alexandra", "slug": "alexandra", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "Queen variety selection, grown in Queensland and other regions", "traits": "Queen-type characteristics, moderate size", "flesh_fruit": "Golden-yellow, aromatic, sweet", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "James Queen", "slug": "james-queen", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "South Africa, also grown in Queensland", "traits": "Large size, dark green leaves with reddish spots", "flesh_fruit": "Reddish-orange flesh on exterior, yellow inside", "yield_notes": "Good", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Queensland Cayenne", "slug": "queensland-cayenne", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 10, "origin": "Queensland, Australia (Queensland Department of Primary Industries), released 1975 after 20 years of breeding and testing", "traits": "Dual-purpose cultivar, specifically bred for Queensland conditions", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow, firm, suitable for both fresh market and canning", "yield_notes": "High, optimized for Queensland climate", "growing_notes": "Specifically developed for humid subtropical climates/Queensland subtropical climate after two decades of research. Dual-purpose for fresh and processing. Represents Queensland''s commitment to pineapple breeding excellence. Well-adapted to local conditions.", "availability": "Queensland Department of Agriculture, heritage collections"}, {"name": "Hilo", "slug": "hilo", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 11, "origin": "Hawaii, USA (selected from Smooth Cayenne in Hilo region), 1960", "traits": "More compact plant than Smooth Cayenne, 3-5 pounds, softer rind, golden flesh", "flesh_fruit": "Golden, juicy, mildly sweet, slightly fibrous", "yield_notes": "Smaller, more cylindrical fruit, numerous suckers, no slips", "growing_notes": "Cayenne variant suitable for humid subtropical climates. Less export-friendly due to softer rind but excellent tropical treat for local fresh markets. Thrives in zones 10-11 with volcanic soil and sun. Good for Humid subtropical subtropical climate.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, tropical fruit collectors"}, {"name": "Sugarloaf (Kona Sugarloaf, White Sugarloaf, Brazilian White)", "slug": "sugarloaf-kona-sugarloaf-white-sugarloaf-brazilian-white", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "West Africa and Hawaii (also known as Pan de Azúcar in Spanish, Pain de Sucre in French), cultivated since 15th century sugar cone era", "traits": "Cylindrical conical shape resembling traditional sugarloaf, 5-6 pounds, green rind remains mostly green when ripe, smooth leaves, softer rind than most varieties", "flesh_fruit": "Creamy white to pale yellow, exceedingly sweet with hints of honey, almost no acidity (lowest acid pineapple), non-stringy, floral aroma, can reach 15° Brix, soft edible core (non-woody)", "yield_notes": "Moderate, 2-3 years to fruit", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Red Spanish (Black Spanish, Large Key, Cuban)", "slug": "red-spanish-black-spanish-large-key-cuban", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 13, "origin": "Caribbean (possibly Hispaniola), spread across Central and South America by Spanish colonizers, historic variety", "traits": "Orange-red to deep red rind, smaller 2-5 pounds, squarish appearance, oval shape, tough skin excellent for shipping, spiny thorny leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Pale-yellow with hints of color, aromatic, fibrous, acidic and bold flavor, pleasant aroma, light yellow", "yield_notes": "1-2 kg, well-adapted for shipping as fresh fruit, moderate to high", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Singapore Red", "slug": "singapore-red", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Malaysia/Singapore region, Spanish group", "traits": "Green leaves with reddish stripe at end, reddish cylindrical fruit, small size", "flesh_fruit": "Golden-yellow", "yield_notes": "Good, disease and pest-resistant", "growing_notes": "Disease and pest resistance makes it excellent for Humid subtropical humid climate. Great for canning. Subtropical adaptation.", "availability": "Specialty Asian variety nurseries, tropical fruit collectors"}, {"name": "Mauritius (Vazhakulam Pineapple, Kannara) 🏆", "slug": "mauritius-vazhakulam-pineapple-kannara", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 0, "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Kew (Giant Kew, Smooth Cayenne)", "slug": "kew-giant-kew-smooth-cayenne", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 1, "origin": "Venezuela (Indians), via Cayenne French Guiana 1820, introduced to India, known as Kew/Sarawak in India", "traits": "Large oblong 2-3 kg, slight taper towards crown, broad shallow eyes ideal for canning, yellow when fully ripe", "flesh_fruit": "Light yellow, juicy, fiberless, firm close-textured", "yield_notes": "High, late-maturing, most popular commercial variety in India, 12-14° Brix, 0.5-1.0% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Queen (Common Rough, Nanas Moris)", "slug": "queen-common-rough-nanas-moris", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 2, "origin": "Widely distributed heritage variety, also called Nanas Moris (Malaysia, from Mauritius name), leading cultivar Philippines, Queensland, South Africa", "traits": "Dwarf plant, short very spiny dark purplish-green leaves, compact, more cold and disease resistant, 1-2.5 pounds, petite, spiky leaves", "flesh_fruit": "Deep golden-yellow, tender, sweeter and more aromatic than Smooth Cayenne, small core, crispy, less juicy but higher quality flavor", "yield_notes": "Average 2 suckers or more for ratooning, 15-16° Brix, 0.6-0.8% acidity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Jaldhup 🏆", "slug": "jaldhup", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "Jaldhup region, India (named after place of maximum production), traditional Indian variety", "traits": "Falls under Queen group, smaller than Queen variety, local type", "flesh_fruit": "Well-balanced blend of sweetness with acidity, alcoholic flavor that can be differentiated from other Queen fruits", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "INDIGENOUS to India. Named after production region. Cultivated for both table and processing purposes. Perfectly adapted to Tropical monsoon tropical monsoon climate with distinctive local flavor profile. Grown in Meghalaya and tropical monsoon climates. Unique alcoholic flavor note distinguishes it.", "availability": "Local tropical monsoon climates markets, Jaldhup region growers, heritage collections"}, {"name": "Lakhat 🏆", "slug": "lakhat", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_