I). Developed for warm climates", "traits": "Large, round, white skin, fleet eyes. Early tuberization in warm climates", "flesh_fruit": "White flesh", "yield_notes": "30 t/ha, fast maturing (75-80 days)", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT for warm climate regions like tropical monsoon climates. Able to build yields rapidly under warmer climate. Primarily cultivated in Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Karnataka. Perfect for processing into chips. Heat-tolerant characteristics.", "availability": "Southern India suppliers, Karnataka/tropical monsoon climates dealers"}, {"name": "Kufri Jawahar", "slug": "kufri-jawahar", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 11, "origin": "India (CPRI), 1996. Cross of Kufri Neelamani × Kufri Jyoti", "traits": "Medium round-oval, creamy white skin, fleet eyes", "flesh_fruit": "Pale yellow flesh", "yield_notes": "40 t/ha, 80-90 days maturity", "growing_notes": "Early maturing variety suitable for intensive cropping systems. Moderately resistant to late blight. Grown in Gujarat, Haryana, Madhya Pradesh, Punjab, Karnataka (southern region). Table purpose variety.", "availability": "Available in Karnataka and surrounding southern states including tropical monsoon climates"}, {"name": "Kufri Chipsona-1", "slug": "kufri-chipsona-1", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "India (CPRI), 1998. Developed for processing", "traits": "Medium to large, oval, white skin, fleet eyes", "flesh_fruit": "Dull white flesh, high dry matter (9.8%)", "yield_notes": "40 t/ha (170-180 qtl/acre), 90-110 days", "growing_notes": "Primarily for making chips and French fries. Resistant to late blight, tolerant to frost. Grown mainly in Bihar and Uttar Pradesh. Excellent keeper. Higher germination percentage. Highest dry matter production suitable for processing industry.", "availability": "Northern India suppliers, available through tropical monsoon climates dealers"}, {"n