 characteristics.", "availability": "CPRI dealers, northern and central India suppliers"}, {"name": "Kufri Pushkar", "slug": "kufri-pushkar", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 17, "origin": "India (CPRI), 2006. Medium maturing", "traits": "White tubers, medium maturing", "flesh_fruit": "Low dry matter (17.4%), table purpose", "yield_notes": "160-170 qtl/acre, 90-100 days", "growing_notes": "Excellent keeper (lowest total weight loss 7.7%). Late wilt disease resistant. Can be stored in normal conditions. Higher germination percentage. Suitable for table purposes. Good marketable yield.", "availability": "Indian seed suppliers nationwide"}, {"name": "Chinese Potato (Plectranthus rotundifolius) - Koorka 🌏 INDIGENOUS", "slug": "chinese-potato-plectranthus-rotundifolius-koorka-indigenous", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 18, "origin": "Indigenous to tropical monsoon climates. Known as ''Koorka'' in Malayalam", "traits": "Small tubers, harder than Irish potato, aromatic", "flesh_fruit": "Unique taste and aroma, desired shape", "yield_notes": "Variable, monsoon crop", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}], "variety_count": 39}'::jsonb,
